.TH WINDOW\-TITLE 1 "2026\-05\-27" "dotfiles" "Window Title Manual"
.SH NAME
window\-title \- fast window title display for sway/waybar (IPC stream)
.SH DESCRIPTION
Displays the focused window's title in a waybar custom module, updated on
every focus or title change.
The title comes straight from sway IPC; for terminals like foot the shell
already encodes
.I "path: context"
(plus a
.I "\ [PID]"
suffix in some prompts) in the window name, so no
.BR /proc " / " pstree
lookups are needed.
.PP
For non\-terminal windows the application's own window title is shown
as\-is (e.g.\& "Inbox \- milojarow@gmail.com \- Betterbird").
.SS Architecture (Method 3, current)
.B window\-title\-stream.py
talks to sway IPC over a persistent UNIX socket \(em the same engine
.B workspaces\-subscribe.py
uses.
It subscribes to
.B window
and
.B workspace
events and prints one JSON line to stdout on each relevant change.
.B waybar
reads that stream directly via
.B custom/window\-title
in stream mode (exec with no interval).
No cache file, no signal\-to\-waybar round\-trip, no
.BR swaymsg / jq
subprocess per event, and no
.BR /proc " / " pstree
inspection.
.PP
If the focused window has a custom label assigned via right\-click rename
(see
.BR "CUSTOM LABELS" )
the label is shown instead of the live title.
.SH DISPLAY FORMAT
The module shows the raw window
.B .name
from sway IPC, escaped for pango markup safety.
Foot encodes
.I "path: context \- shell [pid]"
in its title; GUI apps show whatever they report.
.PP
.B Truncation:
titles longer than 70 characters are truncated with a Unicode ellipsis
.RB ( U+2026 ).
.SH INTERACTIONS
.TP
.B Waybar right\-click
Opens a rofi text input to assign a custom label to the focused window.
A non\-empty submission saves the label;
an empty submission clears it.
The stream daemon is signalled
.RB ( SIGUSR1 )
and re\-emits immediately.
.TP
.B Waybar hover (tooltip)
Shows the application
.B app_id
on the first line and the raw window name on the second.
.SH CUSTOM LABELS
Right\-clicking the waybar module opens a rofi prompt pre\-filled with
either the current override (if one exists) or the live title.
.TP
.B Assign a label
Type the desired text and press
.BR Enter .
The display becomes that text until cleared or the window closes.
.TP
.B Clear a label
Open the prompt and submit an empty string (delete all text, then
.BR Enter ).
The override file is removed and the live title returns.
.TP
.B Cancel
Press
.B Escape
or close rofi \(em no change is made.
.PP
Custom labels are keyed by the sway window ID and live in
.I /tmp/waybar\-window\-names\-$USER/<id>.name
until the window closes.
The stream daemon removes the file on the window
.B close
event, so the entry never outlives the window it labelled.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/window\-title\-stream.py
Stream daemon.
Connects to sway IPC over a persistent UNIX socket, subscribes to
.B window
and
.B workspace
events, and prints one JSON line per change to stdout for waybar's
stream\-mode reader.
Honors per\-window overrides from the names directory.
Handles
.B SIGUSR1
to re\-emit the focused window on demand (used by the rename helper).
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/window\-title\-rename.py
Right\-click handler.
Locates the focused window via
.BR swaymsg ,
opens a rofi prompt pre\-filled with the current label or title, writes
or clears
.IR /tmp/waybar\-window\-names\-$USER/<id>.name ,
then sends
.B SIGUSR1
to the stream daemon.
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc
Waybar module definition
.RI ( custom/window\-title ).
Runs the stream script as
.B exec
without an interval (stream mode),
.B return\-type
.BR json ,
.B on\-click\-right
runs the rename script,
.B tooltip
on,
.B max\-length
70.
.SH PROCESS LIFETIME
The stream is launched and supervised by
.B waybar
itself as the module's
.B exec
command.
There is no
.B exec_always
in sway's autostart, no PID file, and no single\-instance guard:
.B waybar
restarts the script if it exits, and stopping waybar stops the script.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGUSR1
Sent by
.B window\-title\-rename.py
to
.B window\-title\-stream.py
after writing or clearing an override.
Triggers an immediate re\-emit of the focused window's title with the new
label applied.
.SH PROGRAMS
.TP
.B python3
Runtime for both scripts.
Uses only the standard library
.RI ( socket ", " struct ", " json ", " signal ", " html ", " os ).
.TP
.B swaymsg
Called only by
.B window\-title\-rename.py
to fetch the focused window's tree.
The stream daemon uses a raw UNIX socket directly \(em no
.B swaymsg
subprocess per event.
.TP
.B rofi
Launcher used as the text\-input UI for the rename prompt.
.SH STORAGE
All runtime files are in
.I /tmp
and are not persisted across reboots.
.TP
.I /tmp/waybar\-window\-names\-$USER/<id>.name
Per\-window custom label set via right\-click rename.
Cleared by the stream daemon on the window
.B close
event; uncustomized windows simply have no file.
.SH HISTORY
The original implementation was a bash daemon
.RB ( window\-title.sh )
backed by
.BR jq ,
.BR pstree ,
.BR /proc
inspection, a
.I /tmp
JSON cache file, and a left\-click app\-name flash.
.B waybar
polled the cache through a script
.RB ( window\-title\-output.sh )
that ran on every
.B SIGRTMIN+10
signal.
.PP
This pipeline lagged on workspace switches because the per\-event
.BR pstree / ps / readlink
calls landed in the hot path and the cache\(em>signal\(em>exec round\-trip
added latency.
The current Method 3 design replaces the whole stack with a single Python
process that streams JSON straight to waybar over its stdout pipe.
.PP
Removed in the migration: the four
.B .sh
scripts above and the
.B exec_always
entry in
.IR 99\-autostart\-applications.conf .
The left\-click "flash app name for 3 seconds" interaction is also gone;
re\-add it as an
.B on\-click
binding if you miss it.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR waybar (5),
.BR sway (1),
.BR rofi (1),
.BR python3 (1)
